 By now, you should know that attorneys can be considered debt
collectors subject to the Fair  Debt Collection Practices Act =01) even if
the attorney never sends a letter or makes a telephone call, but simply
files a lawsuit.  Litigation against attorneys under the FDCPA is
increasing nationwide, and attorneys are being held liable for even
innocent and technical violations of the FDCPA.  Attend this program to
learn the top 10 ways attorneys violate the FDCPA, and how they can
avoid the violations.  Learning even one new tip could save you in
damages many times the cost of this CLE!

